      <crm:P4_has_time_span>
         <crm:E52_Time-span>
            <crm:P78_is_identified_by>He was a saintly figure from Goǧǧām, a contemporary of ʾaṣe 
                  Yoḥannǝs I and  ʾaṣe
                  ʾIyāsu I. Towards the end of his life, Zarʾa Buruk appears to have been involved in the 
                  Christological controversies of his time. As a result of his disagreeing with ʾaṣe 
                  ʾIyāsu I,  he was imprisoned for five years. 
                  His centre  of veneration is the church dedicated to him, St Michael at Gǝš ʾAbbāy. 
    </crm:P78_is_identified_by>
         </crm:E52_Time-span>
